1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,333
They cut off our hands
and put us in a car

2
00:00:02,416 --> 00:00:04,208
They brought us
to Saddam Hospital

3
00:00:04,958 --> 00:00:06,166
Salam Hospital

4
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:08,833
They let us out

5
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:14,750
The first person was taken to the operating
room, his hand was stitched, and he was sent out

6
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:18,041
I was the second person
to enter the operating room

7
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:24,333
He asked me, do you have any
illnesses or allergies? I said, no

8
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:25,541
The doctor was asking me

9
00:00:25,958 --> 00:00:27,208
I told him, no, I
don’t have any of that

10
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:31,166
He said to me—Sit here, so I sat

11
00:00:32,166 --> 00:00:33,291
Then he said again, No, stand

12
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:35,541
I stood, and he laid
me on a hospital bed

13
00:00:36,458 --> 00:00:38,166
He put a cannula in my hand

14
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:42,791
I don’t know what he injected
me with—seconds later I felt nothing

15
00:00:43,583 --> 00:00:46,583
When I opened my eyes,
I found my hand bandaged

16
00:00:46,625 --> 00:00:47,791
Interviewer: You lost consciousness?
Witness: Yes

17
00:00:48,541 --> 00:00:50,041
When I woke up

18
00:00:52,166 --> 00:00:53,500
I found my hand bandaged

19
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:57,666
I thought to myself, could it be they are
tricking us and didn’t really cut off our hands

20
00:00:59,583 --> 00:01:01,750
When I became a little more
aware, I measured my hands together

21
00:01:01,791 --> 00:01:05,416
And when I saw one was shorter, I knew
they had cut off my hand and I started crying

22
00:01:08,666 --> 00:01:11,000
They gave me a booklet

23
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:17,500
I don’t know what was written in
it—right-hand amputation and so on

24
00:01:18,125 --> 00:01:19,833
I took it and I still
keep it to this day

25
00:01:21,583 --> 00:01:23,166
And they gave me slippers

26
00:01:25,625 --> 00:01:30,291
And they gave me injections to treat
my hand, and said I had to take them

27
00:01:31,666 --> 00:01:32,625
I left

28
00:01:33,791 --> 00:01:35,291
They took us out of the hospital

29
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:38,250
They left— they
brought us and then left

30
00:01:38,291 --> 00:01:40,083
Only one of them stayed
with us until we woke up

31
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:41,791
He gave us these
booklets and left

32
00:01:43,083 --> 00:01:47,833
We left the hospital, and
at the door I hired a taxi

33
00:01:49,916 --> 00:01:53,958
He asked me–Where do you want me
to take you? I said, to the Dawasa area

34
00:01:55,541 --> 00:01:57,541
He said–Where exactly in Dawasa? I
told him, by the governorate building

35
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:03,500
The man I rode with, I didn’t know
him, but he was my father’s friend

36
00:02:06,916 --> 00:02:10,250
When we left the hospital, he started
asking me what had happened and so on

37
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:12,875
So I told him my story

38
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:15,291
The taxi driver started crying

39
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,708
He drove me home

40
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:19,375
And I had no money with me

41
00:02:19,375 --> 00:02:21,791
I said to him—Wait a moment
so I can bring you the fare

42
00:02:22,083 --> 00:02:25,458
He said—No, no, I don't want it,
this is from me, a reward for God

43
00:02:28,541 --> 00:02:31,833
When I stepped out of the
car, I saw my older brother

44
00:02:34,208 --> 00:02:37,750
He said to me—Younes, what happened
to your hand?" I told him—They cut it off

45
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:42,250
He didn’t stop, he started
crying and ran toward the house

46
00:02:43,875 --> 00:02:48,750
While running home he
shouted—Mom, Mom, Younes has come

47
00:02:50,958 --> 00:02:51,916
My mother was overjoyed

48
00:02:52,416 --> 00:02:56,708
And my father came, and she told him—Hajji,
didn’t I tell you he’d return safe

49
00:02:57,041 --> 00:02:58,541
Because that young man came
and told us he’d be released

50
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:02,000
My brother told them—They
freed him, but they’ve cut off his hand

51
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,708
At that moment my father
began hitting his head

52
00:03:08,125 --> 00:03:10,208
As for my mother, I
don’t know what to tell you

53
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:13,541
Thank God in any case

54
00:03:16,916 --> 00:03:18,666
And that’s my story
